<span id="freeTextContainer18411577646807158912">&quot;Ciuraru takes readers on a comprehensive and engaging journey through the minds and careers of more than a dozen famous authors -- including George Sand, Mark Twain, and George Orwell -- who wrote under assumed names. Along the way, we discover not only their reasons, both practical and deeply personal, for obscuring their true identities, but also the peculiar effects that using a pseudonym had on their lives.&quot;</span>
  <span id="freeText18411577646807158912" style="display:none">"Ciuraru takes readers on a comprehensive and engaging journey through the minds and careers of more than a dozen famous authors -- including George Sand, Mark Twain, and George Orwell -- who wrote under assumed names. Along the way, we discover not only their reasons, both practical and deeply personal, for obscuring their true identities, but also the peculiar effects that using a pseudonym had on their lives."</span>
