<div id="review_167731502" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/167731502" />
    <a title="Bri" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2836341-bri"><img alt="Bri" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1524716741p2/2836341.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/167731502?book_show_action=true">May 12, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bri" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bri" href="/user/show/2836341-bri">Bri</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">literary scholars, historians</span></div>

        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2836341-bri?shelf=history">history</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer167731502" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15872480990935221475">I won this book through a Goodreads giveaway and I hate that it took me so long to actually finish it. Real life obligations, however, kept me from enjoying this book at the pace I would have liked.<br/><br/>On a whole, I enjoyed Nom de Plume. Literary scholars may enjoy the topic a bit more but as a historian, the topic was more than enough to keep me interested. Carmela Ciuraru does an excellent job at evoking suitable emotions for each of the life stories relayed in the book. The tone of each section s</span>
  <span id="freeText15872480990935221475" style="display:none">I won this book through a Goodreads giveaway and I hate that it took me so long to actually finish it. Real life obligations, however, kept me from enjoying this book at the pace I would have liked.<br /><br />On a whole, I enjoyed Nom de Plume. Literary scholars may enjoy the topic a bit more but as a historian, the topic was more than enough to keep me interested. Carmela Ciuraru does an excellent job at evoking suitable emotions for each of the life stories relayed in the book. The tone of each section seemed to go along well with the description of each individual's personality. The book was easy to read but it didn't feel "dumbed-down" at all. I learned a great deal about the various authors, including a few authors I'd never heard of before.<br /><br />My one complaint (because you know I'm always going to have one...) is really a minor issue: Ciuraru on occasion seemed to be inconsistent with switching between the pseudonym and the "real" name. Sometimes when this occurred, it seemed to be used to separate the pseudonym from the "real" person, but at other times the switch seemed to be random and could be confusing, especially where multiple people were being referenced. Nothing major that detracted from the overall quality of the book...just a little nitpicky thing of my own.<br /><br />Anywho...good book. I've now added several of the works mentioned within Nom de Plume to my to-read shelf. :)</span>
  <a data-text-id="15872480990935221475" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


